metadata.name: The Collapsing Consciousness
metadata.description: I'm on the verge of losing my mind for good; No dimension could be as terrifying as I'm in it, and finally, this deity, this collapsing consciousness, I have seen whisper the name of where I am: Oth-xa'rath will be your infinity loop, and your bones will remain after you are long gone! I think he had been around for a long, long time, and now he wanted to take me as his prisoner to serve him in this ratchet void. I couldn't move because of his cold blue eyes fixed on me; the creaking sound he made as he turned to me; and the dark mist he spread. This Halloween will be more terrifying than ever!
